Package be.ac.umons.jsonschematools.generator.exploration

Class ExplorationGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • be.ac.umons.jsonschematools.generator.exploration.ExplorationGenerator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IGenerator
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DefaultExplorationGenerator
    public class ExplorationGenerator
extends Object
implements IGenerator
    A generator that produces documents by exhaustively exploring the possibilities described in a JSON schema. If the schema contains a recursive part, an infinite number of documents can be generated. This implementation relies on external classes to handle each type allowed in a JSON schema. See the handlers package for implemented handlers.

      • createIterator

        public Iterator<org.json.JSONObject> createIterator​(be.ac.umons.jsonschematools.JSONSchema schema,
                                                    int maxDocumentDepth,
                                                    boolean canGenerateInvalid)
        Description copied from interface: IGenerator
        Creates an iterator over the documents this generator can produce up to the given document depth. Documents are created when calling next(). The depth of the documents is bounded, i.e., in any document, there can only be at most maxDocumentDepth nested objects and arrays. Note that if the bound is set too low, only invalid documents may be generated as the deepest objects or arrays may not be correct. In particular, no documents will be generated with a depth of zero. Invalid documents can be generated if canGenerateInvalid is true. Note that valid documents can still be generated, no matter the value of canGenerateInvalid.
        Specified by:
        createIterator in interface IGenerator
        Parameters:
        schema - The schema
        maxDocumentDepth - The maximal depth of the documents
        canGenerateInvalid - Whether invalid documents can be generated
        Returns:
        An iterator
